The relational model doesn't prevent programmer fuckups, nor does it save them from many common errors.  For example:<p><pre><code>    sub add_one_to_each_row {
        my $row = shift;
        $row->some_relevant_column( $row->some_relevant_column - 1 );
        $row->update;
    }
</code></pre>
Although the data is fully relational, your program corrupted it anyway.<p>(As a slightly-related aside, I really need to write an essay about how type systems don't prevent bugs when you use overly-broad types like "Integer".)
